cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper presents an operator for interactively exploring a relational table, which falls under the category of data management and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the interaction between the analyst and the system, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category. The use of rules to describe groups of tuples involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. The algorithmic and optimization aspects of the paper suggest that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
